{"data":[{"type":"questionAttempts","id":"17632150","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionAttempts/17632150"},"attributes":{"position":0,"marks":1,"score":0,"answeredAt":"2025-09-30T17:36:58+09:30","options":[1],"response":null,"finalizedAt":"2025-09-30T17:36:58+09:30"},"relationships":{"user":{"data":{"type":"users","id":"50098"}},"questionSession":{"data":null},"session":{"data":null},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"17421"}},"bookmark":{"data":null}}}],"included":[{"type":"questions","id":"17421","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questions/17421"},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"10111"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"70561"}}}},{"type":"items","id":"10111","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/items/10111"},"attributes":{"contentType":"question"},"relationships":{"content":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"17421"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"56025"}},"tags":{"data":[{"type":"tags","id":"67"},{"type":"tags","id":"71"},{"type":"tags","id":"74"},{"type":"tags","id":"5326"},{"type":"tags","id":"5481"}]},"contributions":{"data":[{"type":"contributions","id":"23684"},{"type":"contributions","id":"23689"}]}},"meta":{"canRevise":false,"canManage":false,"canDelete":false}},{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"70561","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionRevisions/70561"},"attributes":{"stem":"\u003Cp\u003ECase reports are an important form of medical literature that contribute to scientific knowledge by documenting unique clinical observations.\u003C/p\u003E","stemQuestion":"Which one of the following best describes the primary purpose of publishing medical case reports?","responseType":"sba","marks":1,"options":["To document novel or unusual clinical observations","To determine disease prevalence in populations","To prove causation between exposures and outcomes","To compare effectiveness of different therapies","To establish treatment guidelines for common conditions"],"correctOptions":[0],"correctResponses":null,"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003EThe primary purpose of case reports is to \u003Cstrong\u003Edocument novel or unusual clinical observations\u003C/strong\u003E. These detailed descriptions of individual cases can highlight previously unknown disease presentations, complications, or treatment responses that may warrant further investigation.\u003C/p\u003E    \u003Cp\u003EThe incorrect options can be explained:\u003C/p\u003E    \u003Cul\u003E        \u003Cli\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003ETo determine disease prevalence in populations\u003C/strong\u003E - This requires epidemiological studies across large population samples to establish accurate frequency estimates.\u003C/li\u003E        \u003Cli\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003ETo prove causation between exposures and outcomes\u003C/strong\u003E - This requires controlled studies with larger sample sizes and statistical analysis to establish causal relationships.\u003C/li\u003E        \u003Cli\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003ETo compare effectiveness of different therapies\u003C/strong\u003E - This requires randomised controlled trials or systematic reviews to evaluate treatment efficacy.\u003C/li\u003E        \u003Cli\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003ETo establish treatment guidelines for common conditions\u003C/strong\u003E - This requires high-level evidence from multiple clinical trials and systematic reviews.\u003C/li\u003E    \u003C/ul\u003E    \u003Cp\u003ECase reports are particularly valuable for identifying rare conditions, unexpected drug effects, or new disease patterns. They often serve as the first indication of emerging clinical phenomena that deserve more rigorous investigation.\u003C/p\u003E","optionExplanations":null,"learningPoints":["Case reports are detailed descriptions of individual patient cases that provide novel or unusual clinical presentations, treatments, or outcomes.","The key components of a case report include patient history, clinical findings, diagnostic assessments, interventions, and outcomes.","Case reports serve as early warning signals for rare diseases, adverse drug effects, or emerging health threats."],"references":["Shultz JM, Sullivan LM, Galea S. Public Health: An Introduction to the Science and Practice of Population Health. Springer Publishing Company; 2021.","Ray, Sumantra, and others (eds), Oxford Handbook of Clinical and Healthcare Research, 1, Oxford Medical Handbooks (Oxford, 2016; online edn, Oxford Academic, 1 Mar. 2016), https://doi.org/10.1093/med/9780199608478.001.0001, accessed 12 Dec. 2024."]},"relationships":{"itemRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"56025"}},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"17421"}},"stemMedia":{"data":[]},"explanationMedia":{"data":[]}}},{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"56025","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/itemRevisions/56025"},"attributes":{"createdAt":"2024-12-15T19:18:02+10:30","updatedAt":"2025-01-04T00:09:15+10:30"},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"10111"}},"content":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"70561"}}},"meta":{"canDelete":false}},{"type":"tags","id":"67","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/67"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Basic Science","synonyms":null,"description":null,"position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"5"}},"heading":{"data":null}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"71","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/71"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Junior","synonyms":null,"description":"Suitable for a junior, pre-clinical medical student","position":0,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"6"}},"heading":{"data":null}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"74","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/74"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Level I","synonyms":null,"description":"Remember (identifying and retri